> What's not to love about the classic hoagie (or sub, or grinder, or wedge) filled
> with savory steak, lightly charred veggies, and melty cheese? Our homage to the
> classic sando boasts saucy diced steak, a blanket of melty mozz, sautéed onion
> and bell pepper, and garlic mayo all stuffed inside garlic-butter-brushed
> baguettes. One bite will have you head over heels.

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice
@Long Green Pepper{1} crosswise into strips.

== Roasted Potato Wedges ==

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{drizzle of},
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Garlic Mayo ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with
@Garlic Powder{1/4%tsp} (add up to ½ tsp if you like; you'll use more later).
Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

== Garlic Baguettes ==

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @Yellow Onion{1}(thinly sliced) and
@Long Green Pepper{1}(thinly sliced); cook, stirring occasionally, until softened
and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, place @Butter{2%tablespoon} and @Garlic Powder{1/4%tsp} (add more if
desired) in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until just
softened, ~{10%seconds}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}; stir
to combine.

Slice @Demi-Baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through;
spread garlic butter onto cut sides. Place cut sides up on a second baking
sheet.

Toast on middle rack of oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Pepper Steak ==

Pat @Diced Steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in #pan{} used for veggies over high heat. Add steak
and @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until steak is browned and
cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{2%tablespoon}.
Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Return cooked veggies to pan; stir to combine.

== Assembly ==

Spread bottom halves of garlic buns with half the garlic mayo. Top with steak
and veggie mixture, then sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Return to oven until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide sandos and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining garlic mayo on
the side.